and household-scale logging operations, and the dramatic effects of consumer culture and the global shift toward fossil fuels on settlers’ ability to control the tourism economy after 1900. Making Muskoka uncovers the lived experience of rural communities shaped by tourism at a time when sustainable opportunities for a sedentary life were few on the Canadian Shield, and reveals the consequences for those living there year-round.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRural developmentzOntariozMuskoka (District municipality)xHistoryy19th century. 0aRural developmentzOntariozMuskoka (District municipality)xHistoryy20th century. 0aSustainable developmentzOntariozMuskoka (District municipality)xHistoryy19th century. 0aSustainable developmentzOntariozMuskoka (District municipality)xHistoryy20th century. 0aTourismzOntariozMuskoka (District municipality)xHistoryy19th century. 0aTourismzOntariozMuskoka (District municipality)xHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Geography.2bisacsh1 aWynn, Graeme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311141763940uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486785640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774867856423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774867856/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-141763-9  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles